H(X)=(\log 6)/(\log 2),\qquad  H(Y)=1.
I(X;Y)=H(X)+H(Y)-H(X,Y)=\frac{\log 6}{\log 2} + 1 - \frac{\log 6}{\log 2}=1:
H(X,Y)=H(X)\ \ \  \Rightarrow\ \ \  I(X;Y)=H(Y).
 H(X\mid Y)=H(X,Y)-H(Y)=\frac{\log 6}{\log 2}-1=\frac{\log 3}{\log 2}: 
